<h4><a href="/home.html"> Home </a href>  <a href="/CPU.html"> CPU </a href></h4><h3><strong>The steps to disassemble an HP MXI8380ZPN</h3>
<li>Find the right tools.(star head,screwdrivers,phillips head.)
</li>
<li>Find the buttons on side of the case.
</li>
<li>Unscrew the RAM, refer to the image below, using a screwdriver.</li>
<li>Slide the RAM out of the case.</li>
<li>Press the button on the CD-ROM Drive as shown below.</li>
<li>Take the CD-ROM Drive out of the case.</li>
<li>Unscrew the RAM Fan using a screwdriver.</li>
<li>Lift the RAM Fan from the case.</li>
<li>Unscrew the cables using a screwdriver from the back of the case.</li>
<li>Unplug the cables from their respective parts.</li>
<li>Take the cables out of the case.</li>
<li>Use a screwdriver to take the screws out of the CD-ROM Drive’s Holder.</li>
<li>Take out the CD-ROM Drive’s Holder.</li>
<li>Slide the other fans out of the case.</li>
<li>Unscrew the screws of the Motherboard with a Screwdriver.</li>
<li>Take the Motherboard out of the case.</li>
<li>Unlatch the Hard Drive.</li>
<li>Take out the Hard Drive.</li>
<li> And that's about it, if you want to take apart each individual thing you can but be warned you might not be able to put them back together.</li>
